This is my latest map DE_Star a futuristic themed map for CS:S. Based on a landing platform above a huge city, the map has been purposely built small to keep play fast and too the point.

The texture set is 99% custom and comes with custom soundscapes to create as unique experience as possible. The map is fully BSP zipped for easy server sharing, fully support HDR and comes with bot support. This is my first CS:S map and my first release for over a year.

=======
Briefing
=======

A dark cloud is growing over Neon City, the fanatical terrorist organization 'The blah' has been destroying key locations important to trade and tourism. The most important locations are Neon's 4 Star platforms, floating landing ports that transfer goods and civilians to larger capital ships, destined for deep space.

Now the blah have contacted the Mayor of Neon City threatening to destroy Neon's last Star Platform, crippling the economy in the immediate area, unless there demands are met. All civilians have been allowed to leave, though many lives are still in danger in the city below.

CT's must stop the 'blah' by defending the platforms entrance which is known to have weak supports and the platforms core without this the platform would simply fall from the sky causing untold damage.

With there demands refused T's must destroy the platform in order to strike a blow to Neons economy. Destroy the main entrance area, or destroy the core which will send the platform spiraling towards the City.

=======
Special Thanks
=======

General

I needed a project, so I chose to remake one of my favorite maps from Counter-Strike: Condition Zero. This took 3-4 weeks to get into it's first Beta stage. It's far from being complete, as there are still some texture, lighting, or game play tweaks that need to be done. I went all out with this project. I used a couple custom textures, fine-tuned the .nav, and even made a custom radar.

Gameplay

I've tested the map so far with bots, and it seems to play like the original. There are still some issues, such as the bots will not use the vending machines by bombsite A to reach it, even though I've made the area myself in the .nav. They tend to use the staircase which takes longer, or go straight to bombsite B, which is where most of the firefights occur. Hopefully in later versions I can address this so the map doesn't get boring.

by DA!M

First of all, this is my first big mapping project. Until this map i was always working on aim/fy_maps.
So there are different things i didn't knew about and which this map don't contain!
 
And i must say that i didn't spend to mutch time on optimization..=(! I thought that this would be possible within a week, but when i saw all the tutorials about hint-brushes and so on, it was impossible for me to do all theses optimization-things in one week, i'm sorry for that ^^)

So enough bad news (D!

____________________________

I first thought about remaking de_inferno Halloween-themed but later i decide to make something totally new!
It is an multiplayer-map and i read a lot about how to design a well balanced map with a interesting game play-feeling. So here it is: 

###  The Story

The basic style of the map is oriented on de_inferno, cs_italy and cs_militia. The _style_, not the _buildup_!

It takes place in an old, rainy village (like de_inferno). The denizens have already decorated their homes for Halloween, with pumpkins (my first models ;D), garlands and some pictures, drawn on the walls.

Seems to be a happy Halloween party this year.

But today, the night of the 31st of October, something is happening in the tiny village...
The old flares in the castle ruins start burning, there paranormal noises in the forest and blood in a shed...

Beasts came over the village. They killed all life they found and are no creeping around...

So the politicians decided to send a special-ops team to the hamlet and strike back. They can't know that a global terrorism group is interested in the monsters and trying to catch some of them for their dark plans.

As a necessary result a battle to death break out between both fractions and now Cts are fighting Ts in that lost village with its shy but killy creatures...
and your are going to join this battle!

### The Atmosphere

I've tried to make a map which has a deep, affecting atmosphere but is also well playable! So i had to make some concessions to lightning and to the amount and loudness of sounds. Creating the soundscapes took me about a week, but I'm proud of the result =D! 

For a realistic, "living" illusion of the Village, i used many sequences, some referring to the players movement and acting, some starting automatically. I highly recommend to play the map alone without bots or other players and sneak the whole time! Try to find every hidden event, the following video may be a help:

<iframe width="560" height="315" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/oOBdZV55XhQ" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>

### Additional 

All instructions about installing, credits and thanks can be found in the readme-file, packed to the map.

I recommend to overwrite the detail.vbsp file I've included with the existing one in your cstrike folders. The one i added contains all detail-sprites the engine currently uses, it was overwritten with the last update and doesn't work any more! 

I think that was all i wanted to say, now download the map and have a scary time ;D.

Lukas 'DA!M' B.

PS: I hope i packed all files correctly to the bsp file =S...

PPS: Fog fucks up the screenshots...sry for that!

_aLatestUpdates._sText:
<u>Update changelog (December 16, 2013)</u>
-----------------------------------

- The clip system is rebuilt from scratch to prevent players from having any chance to boost/buddy-jump into balconies or non-playable areas (Thanks to UKCS community for bringing this issue to my attention)
- Many static props are turned to non-solid to enhance gameplay and make player movement smooth and fluid (gutter pipes, rails, lanterns). Many small physics props are updated with the "debris" flag to avoid annoying interaction with the player while moving on/near these props.
- Minor graphical updates are carried on with regard to realigning or readjusting certain textures on curves and cylinders-shaped brushes.
- The optimization system is further improved by adding a couple of additional areaportals and hint brushes.
- Minor lighting glitches are fixed after they were introduced with the Steampipe update of Counter-Strike Source. 


If you load the map in Counter-Strike source and can't see reflections/shiny surfaces, then open the console (~) and type mat_specular 1 to enable reflections.

<font size="3">Spezia - Bomb/Defuse</font>
------------------

<font size="3">By Will2k</font>
------------------

<u>Update changelog (December 16, 2013)</u>

- The clip system is rebuilt from scratch to prevent players from having any chance to boost/buddy-jump into balconies or non-playable areas (Thanks to UKCS community for bringing this issue to my attention)
- Many static props are turned to non-solid to enhance gameplay and make player movement smooth and fluid (gutter pipes, rails, lanterns). Many small physics props are updated with the "debris" flag to avoid annoying interaction with the player while moving on/near these props.
- Minor graphical updates are carried on with regard to realigning or readjusting certain textures on curves and cylinders-shaped brushes.
- The optimization system is further improved by adding a couple of additional areaportals and hint brushes.
- Minor lighting glitches are fixed after they were introduced with the Steampipe update of Counter-Strike Source.

If you load the map in Counter-Strike source and can't see reflections/shiny surfaces, then open the console (~) and type mat\_specular 1 to enable reflections.

For updated visuals and layout and greatly improved gameplay, be sure to check the [CSGO](http://csgo.gamebanana.com/maps/172542 "") version.

Enjoy the updated map.

Will2k

December 16, 2013
<HR SIZE=2 WIDTH="100%" ALIGN=CENTER color="#ffffff">

De_spezia (pronounced "Spetsia") is a bomb/defuse map inspired by several ancient towns in the province of La Spezia in Liguria, northern Italy. The map is not an accurate recreation but rather an inspiration from the towns of La Spezia, Porto Venere and the five towns that constitute the marvelous Cinque Terre (Riomaggiore, Manarola, Corniglia, Vernazza, Monterosso al Mare)

Each town contributed to the map with streets layouts, buildings architecture and colors, historical landmarks, decorations and vegetations and so on. I used reference photos from the internet as well as some of my photos from my last trip to Italy. The 3D skybox has actual photos from Manarola and Vernazza.

The map is large and detailed but very easy to navigate and remember. I was constantly compiling and re-tweaking it to stay within the limits of the source engine; that's why I had to discard many details from the real world locations for the sake of gameplay and framerate. The map has also been optimised to the best possible extent to ensure fluid gameplay and consistent high FPS.

The map has:

- 64 spawn points (32 vs 32)
- radar overview
- 3D skybox
- Soundscapes
- custom textures and models
- nav file for bots navigation with place names 
All the custom resources (except the nav) are embedded in the bsp.

For installation, simply extract the files in the zip archive (bsp, nav and txt files) to your \Counter-Strike Source\cstrike\maps folder.

This project was supposed to be finished in a 2 months period but it actually took 8 months on and off. It was like work on the map for 1 week then stop for 2 months then go back again :(
It was a bit exhausting since I also did my own textures (Photoshop and VTFedit) and experimented with lots of textures and models before settling on the final ones but I enjoyed every bit of it and I'm rather satisfied with the outcome.

I really hope you enjoy this map as much as I did creating it.
Comments and constructive feedback are always welcome.

Will2k

September 22, 2011
